HEALTH ASSISTANT AI

OVERVIEW

Health Assistant AI is an intelligent healthcare support agent built on Agentforce using Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG). The agent utilizes information from the patient.txt knowledge source and the Patient Q&A Cheat Sheet stored in the Agentforce Data Library to answer user health-related questions accurately and safely.

The primary goal of this agent is to understand user symptoms, identify possible health concerns, provide basic guidance, suggest appropriate doctor specializations, and answer medicine-related questions using the available knowledge base.

---

FEATURES

Symptom Analysis

The agent can understand and analyze symptoms described by users and identify possible common health conditions.

Allergy Support

The agent can provide information related to:

• Existing allergies

• Allergic reactions

• Medicine allergies

• Unknown medicine usage concerns

Medical Query Assistance

The agent can answer general health and medical questions including:

• Disease symptoms

• Common health concerns

• Basic healthcare guidance

• Preventive health measures

Medicine Information

The agent can provide information about medicines available in its knowledge source and answer medicine-related queries.

Doctor Recommendation

Based on the user's symptoms and health concerns, the agent can recommend the most suitable doctor specialization and suggest doctors from the available doctor list.

---

TECHNOLOGY USED

Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)

The agent uses RAG architecture to retrieve relevant healthcare information from the knowledge base before generating responses.

Agentforce Data Library

Connected Resources:

• patient.txt

• Patient Q&A Cheat Sheet

These resources serve as the primary knowledge source for healthcare-related responses.

---

CLASSIFICATION DESCRIPTION

The agent classifies and addresses user inquiries related to identifying potential health issues based on symptoms provided by users.

---

SCOPE

The Health Assistant AI is designed to:

• Understand symptoms described by users

• Ask clarifying questions when necessary

• Identify possible common health conditions

• Provide basic healthcare guidance

• Suggest suitable doctor specializations

• Answer medicine-related questions using available knowledge

The agent does not provide medical diagnoses and does not replace professional medical consultation.

---

USER INTERACTION PROCESS

1. Ask the user to describe symptoms in detail.

2. Analyze the provided symptoms.

3. Ask follow-up questions if additional information is required.

4. Identify possible common conditions.

5. Provide basic precautions and lifestyle recommendations.

6. Suggest common OTC medicines when appropriate.

7. Recommend the correct doctor specialization.

8. Suggest a doctor from the available doctor list when needed.

